            <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-200 mb-4">Options
              Contracts</h3>
            <p class="text-base text-slate-400">An options contract gives
              the holder the *right*, but not the obligation, to buy (call
              option) or sell (put option) an underlying asset at a specified
              price (strike price) on or before a certain date. This 'right, not
              obligation' feature provides flexibility and limits risk to the
              premium paid, but potential returns can be significant.</p>
          </div>
