            <p class="text-base text-slate-400">Similar to futures, a forward
              contract is a customized agreement between two parties to buy or
              sell an asset at a specified price on a future date. Unlike
              futures, forwards are over-the-counter (OTC) agreements, meaning
              they are not traded on an exchange, offering greater customization
              but also higher counterparty risk.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
